The paper focuses on the interaction between humans and mobile robots in a human-centered environment, specifically in a smart home environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an interaction method that leverages cameras to perceive laser spots, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
